 wt(PKG/'00_EXECUTIVE_VERDICT.md',f'''# QM28 Executive Verdict\n\n`WINDOW=QM28 | SNAPSHOT={SNAP} | INPUT_MODE=QUANT_EXECUTE/COHORT_BUILD`\n\nHeat treatment is not a portable scalar in Ti/TMCs. The complete sequence, beta-transus relation, cooling path, metastable matrix state, precipitates and reinforcement-mediated grain-boundary transformation jointly determine the sign.\n\nThree primary papers yielded {len(obs)} atomic rows and {len(pairs)} class-A same-paper pairs. In 2018 extruded 5.1 vol% TiBw/near-alpha Ti, four routes raised 600 °C UTS 850→904-986 MPa (+6.4% to +16.0%) while elongation fell 15.5→14.5-10.8%. In 2024 rolled 3.5 vol% TiB/(TA15-Si), 1050 °C/30 min/WQ+600 °C/1 h/AC produced the optimum 600 °C UTS 710→992 MPa (+282 MPa; +39.7%) and hardness 422→482 HV, but strain fell 39→26%. At 700-750 °C aging, martensite decomposed and abnormal alpha growth reduced the UTS gain to +142/+58 MPa; 750 °C aging reduced hardness below as-rolled. At 700 °C test, UTS rose 228→399-421 MPa while strain fell 182→68%.\n\nThe decisive interaction is the 2021 LPBF 2×2: 1050 °C/2 h/FC changed rupture time 3.4→0.6 h in Ti64 but 2.9→5.8 h in TiB/Ti64. Additive HT×reinforcement interaction = +5.7 h; ratio-of-ratios = 11.33. Continuous GB-alpha explains Ti64 collapse; TiB suppresses that network and adds equiaxed alpha, interfaces and load transfer.\n\nPaper-equal descriptive ΔUTS at 600 °C across two tensile paper families = {eq:.1f} MPa; discrete k=2 cluster interval {lo:.1f}-{hi:.1f} MPa. Formal random effects/prediction interval are NOT_IDENTIFIABLE; LOPO range {min(pm.values()):.1f}-{max(pm.values()):.1f} MPa.\n\nClaim ceiling: level 2, same-paper paired association/controlled 2×2 interaction. No ACTIVE/Gold mutation, production-model registration, platform retraining or VALIDATED formulation. Structurally complete for opened evidence; canonical V29 archive ingestion remains a data gap.''')
 wt(PKG/'METHODS.md',f'''# Methods\n\nAtomic unit: paper × sample × actual composition × precursor/reinforcement × process × ordered heat-treatment sequence × microstructure × test mode/temperature/stress/rate/orientation × property. No route was collapsed to maximum temperature.\n\nEstimands: ΔY=Y_HT−Y_baseline; lnRR=ln(Y_HT/Y_baseline); percent change; additive and multiplicative HT×reinforcement interaction. All pairs are class A. Individual CIs were not fabricated because arm SD/SE is absent. The 600 °C UTS summary averages routes within paper, papers equally, then uses 20,000 paper-cluster bootstrap draws (seed {SEED}); k=2 makes the interval discrete/exploratory and prediction intervals/tau²/I² not identifiable. LOPO equals leave-family-out here.\n\nDose variables preserve temperature, time, cooling and beta-transus relation. Only observed points are plotted; no unsupported interpolation. The 2021 2×2 DID is an association, not randomized causality. No p-value family was generated, so BH-FDR is not applicable. Plot scripts read figure_data CSVs and emit SVG/PDF/600 dpi PNG.''')
 wt(PKG/'LIMITATIONS.md','''# Limitations\n\n1. Canonical V29 atomic/provenance/condition assets and uploaded archive bytes were not accessible because the execution backend rejected archive sessions; this is a derived, non-authoritative snapshot.\n2. Three independent quantitative papers; two comparable tensile families. Formal hierarchical/dose models are not identifiable.\n3. Original byte hashes are missing for File Library PDFs; normalized capture hashes are typed explicitly.\n4. Arm SD/SE is absent; point contrasts have no fabricated CI.\n5. 2018 500/550 °C caption conflict is preserved; Table 1 is authoritative.\n6. 2024 750 °C-aged elongation is missing; no imputation/digitization.\n7. Exact relative beta-transus is available only for 2024 (+30 °C); cooling rates are labels, not measured rates.\n8. Creep interaction is specific to LPBF Ti64/TiB-Ti64 at 600 °C/200 MPa.\n9. Claim level ≤2; no Gold/ACTIVE/model/formulation promotion.''')
 req={'window_id':'QM28','current_snapshot_id':SNAP,'status':'CONTINUE_DATA_GAP','required_inputs':[{'name':'V29_ATOMIC_RECORDS','patterns':['**/ATOMIC_RECORDS.csv','**/ATOMIC_RECORDS.parquet'],'reason':'authoritative cohort/all pairs'},{'name':'V29_PROVENANCE','patterns':['**/PROVENANCE.jsonl'],'reason':'original hashes/locators'},{'name':'CONDITION_MANIFEST','patterns':['**/condition_canonical_manifest*.csv'],'reason':'full route/cooling normalization'},{'name':'SOURCE_RELIABILITY','patterns':['**/source_reliability*.csv','**/quality_domain*.csv'],'reason':'evidence weighting'},{'name':'PAPER_REGISTRY','patterns':['**/paper*registry*.csv'],'reason':'duplicate control'},{'name':'REPLICATE_UNCERTAINTY','patterns':['**/*replicate*.csv','**/*uncertainty*.csv'],'reason':'CI/hierarchical model'},{'name':'ORIGINAL_BYTE_HASHES','patterns':['**/CHECKSUMS.sha256','**/MANIFEST.json'],'reason':'replace normalized capture hashes'}],'archives_to_scan':['/mnt/data/'+n for n in archives],'minimum_required_fields':['snapshot_id','source_hash','paper_uid','sample_uid','condition_uid','full_heat_treatment_sequence','beta_transus_C','cooling_rate_or_label','property','value','unit','test_temperature_C','test_mode','replicate_n','sd_or_se'],'local_actions':['CRC/testzip/SHA all archives without repacking','extract canonical QM28 rows','rerun recompute/tests/plots','do not promote ACTIVE/Gold until closure']}; wj(PKG/'WEB_TO_LOCAL_REQUEST.json',req)
 wt(PKG/'LOCAL_ABSORPTION_PROMPT.md',f'''# Local absorption prompt — QM28\n\nVerify ZIP CRC and `sha256sum -c CHECKSUMS.sha256`. Preserve source archives unchanged. Resolve `WEB_TO_LOCAL_REQUEST.json` against V29; replace normalized hashes with original byte SHA and bind every row to snapshot/source/paper/sample/condition. Merge only into `q40/QM28`; do not modify ACTIVE_TITMC, Gold, Schema or model registry. Run `python analysis_code/recompute_qm28.py`, unit tests and four plot scripts. Compare rows/estimands/figure-data hashes; never overwrite conflicts silently. Current derived snapshot: `{SNAP}`.''')
